OL,5, Marshall lives in west Jackson, in the 
OL,6, US state of Mississippi - a            
OL,7, predominantly black and poor part of   
OL,8, the city. He has no choice but to drink
OL,9, the tap water that Jackson residents   
OL,10, have been told to avoid. When he turns 
OL,11, the tap on - the water runs brown.     
OL,13,FHe says it's been like this for about  
OL,14,Feight months and he has no choice but  
OL,15,Fto drink it.                           
OL,17,F"Yes ma'am. I been drinking it." He    
OL,18,Fsmiles when we ask whether it worries  
OL,19,Fhim. "I turn 70 later this month," he  
OL,20,Fsays.                                  
